# Frontend config. Copy to `.env.local` for local dev.
#
# SAME-ORIGIN by default (Slice 17, #46): in production the app and API share one
# origin — serve.mjs (the production host) reverse-proxies /api/* to the API — so
# the app calls RELATIVE /api paths and needs no API URL. In dev, `vite dev`
# proxies /api the same way (see vite.config.ts). You normally set nothing here.

# --- Build-time (VITE_-prefixed, baked into the browser bundle) --------------
# Optional override of the API origin. Leave UNSET for the same-origin proxy
# setup (production and normal dev). Set it only to point a build straight at a
# remote API without the proxy, e.g. VITE_API_URL=https://api.example.com
# VITE_API_URL=

# Optional: where `vite dev` proxies /api to (default http://localhost:8080).
# VITE_DEV_API_URL=http://localhost:8080

# --- Runtime (serve.mjs in production only; NOT a build var) ------------------
# Origin of the API service that serve.mjs forwards /api/* to. Set this in the
# Railway FRONTEND service's Variables, e.g.
#   API_URL=https://oapcmgenerator-production.up.railway.app
